00:05:47.180 --> 00:05:50.340
length root pi.

00:05:50.340 --> 00:05:51.780
Absolutely.

00:05:51.780 --> 00:05:57.080
So to the modern day people,
with our tools of algebra--

00:05:57.080 --> 00:05:58.390
algebra is fantastic.

00:05:58.390 --> 00:06:00.550
People complain about algebra,
and having to

00:06:00.550 --> 00:06:02.340
learn algebra at school.

00:06:02.340 --> 00:06:05.470
But if we didn't have algebra,
we would be doing maths like

00:06:05.470 --> 00:06:07.710
the Ancient Greeks did maths.

00:06:07.710 --> 00:06:10.950
I promise you, that would
be much, much worse.

00:06:10.950 --> 00:06:14.090
Your textbooks would
be ridiculous.

00:06:14.090 --> 00:06:16.440
They'd be very wordy.

00:06:16.440 --> 00:06:19.640
Algebra is an amazing, powerful
tool in mathematics.

00:06:19.640 --> 00:06:22.080
It's not there to cause
you problems.

00:06:22.080 --> 00:06:23.290
It's there for a reason.

00:06:23.290 --> 00:06:24.750
It's brilliant.

00:06:24.750 --> 00:06:30.980
So this is easy to make a square
with the area of pi.

00:06:30.980 --> 00:06:36.050
But using the Greek rules,
straight lines and circles,

00:06:36.050 --> 00:06:37.900
it's impossible to do.

00:06:37.900 --> 00:06:40.280
BRADY: You say it's easy
